item.title: CVE-2023-3346|2024-08-02T06:55:02.703Z -- mitsubishi%20electric%20corporation -- mitsubishi%20cnc%20m800v%20series%20m800vw
item.description: Buffer Copy without Checking Size of Input ('Classic Buffer Overflow') vulnerability in MITSUBSHI CNC Series allows a remote unauthenticated attacker to cause Denial of Service (DoS) condition and execute arbitrary code on the product by sending specially crafted packets. In addition, system reset is required for recovery.
